---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Hankyeol Kyung">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="eyebrow">AI systems · runtime · deployment</div>
    <h1>Building practical systems for memory, runtime, and human-AI collaboration.</h1>
    <p class="hero-lede">
      I work on AI systems that have to survive real workflows, not only demos.
      My work sits across product surfaces and the infrastructure underneath them:
      SleepHub, agent infrastructure, and knowledge systems that accumulate context over time.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <span class="section-label">Current focus</span>
    <ul class="now-list">
      <li><strong>Ambient AI that earns its place.</strong> Building bedside and background systems that stay useful without becoming noisy.</li>
      <li><strong>Agent runtime and memory.</strong> Making state, continuity, guardrails, and tool use hold up across real sessions.</li>
      <li><strong>Validation surfaces.</strong> Thinking about how AI products move from internal prototypes to practical deployment, testbeds, and real users.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <span class="section-label">What I'm building</span>

    <div class="project">
      <h3><a href="/projects#sleephub">SleepHub</a></h3>
      <p>Ambient bedside AI at Asleep. Core loop: understand what happened during the night, then turn that into useful daytime action.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h3><a href="/projects#agent-infra">Agent infrastructure</a></h3>
      <p>Runtime correctness, session continuity, harness engineering, and structured control over agents in real workflows.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h3><a href="/projects#knowledge-os">Knowledge OS</a></h3>
      <p>A markdown-first personal memory substrate, with this site as a curated public layer rather than a raw dump.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <span class="section-label">What I believe</span>
    <ol class="belief-list">
      <li>
        <span class="num">01</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Runtime is the product.</strong>
          <p>Most AI systems fail in the seams: retries, state handoffs, partial context, and 3am behavior. The product is what happens there.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="num">02</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Memory should be explicit.</strong>
          <p>If you can't read, inspect, and revise the memory layer, you can't trust what the agent is doing with it.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="num">03</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Ambient beats intrusive.</strong>
          <p>The best AI systems earn attention by being useful quietly. They fit the workflow instead of interrupting it.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="num">04</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Deployment matters more than posture.</strong>
          <p>The question is not whether a system sounds impressive, but whether it can survive contact with real operators, real users, and real constraints.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <span class="section-label">Where to go next</span>
    <div class="entry-grid">
      <a class="entry-card" href="/direction">
        <h3>Direction</h3>
        <p>The thesis, current focus, and the problems I actually want to spend years on.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="entry-card" href="/projects">
        <h3>Projects</h3>
        <p>Work across SleepHub, agent infrastructure, personal memory systems, and practical tooling.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="entry-card" href="/writing">
        <h3>Writing</h3>
        <p>Notes on agents, memory, product direction, and the systems layer under applied AI.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="entry-card" href="/about">
        <h3>About</h3>
        <p>How I think about harnesses, interfaces, structured control, and collaboration with AI.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
